<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
	{{> header}}
	<body>
		<div id="main" class="container">
			<h1>API Basejump: File Metadata</h1>
			<hr>
			<div id="text">
				<h4>Description:</h4> 
				<p>With this microservice you can check the size (in bytes) of any file on your computer. Go to <b>/api</b>, choose which file you are curious about and click Check Size. This will not save or log your file anywhere; simply return an object with the value in bytes.</p>
				<br>
				<h4>Usage:</h4>
				<p class="bg-info">Browse for a file like "randomText.txt" or "funnyCatPicture.png" on your computer and click 'Check Size'</p>
				<h4>Output:</h4>
				<p class="bg-danger">{ size: 7986 }</p>
			</div>
		</div>
	</body>
</html>
